{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-detail-page-js","path":"/behaviour-at-work/how-to-behave-at-work","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Buckinghamshire HR service desk","basePath":"https://bucks-temp-name.com","gaConfig":{"id":"UA-129132977-3"}}},"contentfulPage":{"title":"How to behave at work","metaTitle":"How to behave at work","metaDescription":"Find out how we are expected to conduct ourselves while working for the council, based on our code of conduct. ","parentPage":{"slug":"behaviour-at-work","title":"Behaviour at work"},"intro":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>How we behave and conduct ourselves at work is important. Our Code of Conduct is based on the idea that everyone who works here treats each other with dignity and respect. </p>\n<p>All of us, managers and employees, have a duty to behave well at work. Your manager should make sure you know how you’re expected to behave to work. </p>\n<p>The principles of how we behave are written down in detail in our <a href=\"//assets.ctfassets.net/fxzi1pcakms5/gN5IUSKGMQu2kP09foE8M/daf18a09bcfc8578851e299c884d5cd8/BC_Code_of_Conduct_Services_Mar_2020__1_.rtf\">Code of Conduct</a>, but this page gives an overview of how we’re expected to behave. </p>"}},"body":null,"hero":{"headline":"Dealing with poor behaviour hero","subHeading":null,"image":[{"title":"Poor behaviour large","description":"1440","file":{"details":{"size":60966,"image":{"width":1440,"height":450}},"fileName":"behaviour--1440.jpg","contentType":"image/jpeg","url":"//images.ctfassets.net/fxzi1pcakms5/3nPEF8QrblcmyHuFoe6SXo/8f0c858b8a2d4c806ae29126e93e2cf9/behaviour--1440.jpg"}},{"title":"Poor behaviour medium","description":"800","file":{"details":{"size":30847,"image":{"width":800,"height":375}},"fileName":"behaviour--800.jpg","contentType":"image/jpeg","url":"//images.ctfassets.net/fxzi1pcakms5/6upmfU1DrD0Pg4wMPAXOD8/96f4415a24250ce0ee9666f2a2f6cac5/behaviour--800.jpg"}},{"title":"Poor behaviour small","description":"440","file":{"details":{"size":17070,"image":{"width":440,"height":300}},"fileName":"behaviour--440.jpg","contentType":"image/jpeg","url":"//images.ctfassets.net/fxzi1pcakms5/2nqFX8YmVvsJkMIvHKrnvK/cc5d96a0b7196699b5cc8116b2e442ad/behaviour--440.jpg"}}]},"collapsibleLinks":[{"title":"Safeguarding children and vulnerable people","ariaLabel":null,"content":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Anyone who works with children, young people or adults with care and support needs has a duty to keep them safe. </p>\n<p>Please read our <a href=\"//assets.ctfassets.net/fxzi1pcakms5/3ANfbzjWTXEvIkpNh4PMbl/e375157eb0bdba249811c70a1ac66683/BC_Code_of_Conduct_Services_Mar_2020.docx\" title=\"Code of Conduct\">Code of Conduct and Appendices</a> to find out more.</p>"}},"open":null,"link":null,"mediaLink":null},{"title":"Respecting personal data and confidentiality","ariaLabel":null,"content":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>All personal data and information should be respected and kept safe. This includes any personal information about councillors. You should never:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Use information for your own personal gain or pass it on to other people</li>\n<li>Record a meeting without consent</li>\n<li>Post sensitive information about a colleague or the council on social media without them knowing</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We all sign a confidentiality agreement when we join the council to say you will follow our policy on personal data.</p>"}},"open":null,"link":null,"mediaLink":null},{"title":"Commercial business","ariaLabel":null,"content":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>All council business should be carried out to high standards. You must follow the law in anything commercial or business related and never take part in fraud or corruption.</p>\n<p>Read our <a href=\"//assets.ctfassets.net/fxzi1pcakms5/1G8aA86Li73BbNwCmorurO/b40cfbce73dd92a5e6d64d2293db7976/Anti-fraud_and_Corruption_Policy_v1.2.rtf\" title=\"Anti Fraud and Corruption Policy\">Anti-fraud and Corruption Policy</a>.</p>"}},"open":null,"link":null,"mediaLink":null},{"title":"Close personal relationships at work","ariaLabel":null,"content":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>We won’t interfere in your private life unless it is having an effect on council services or could damage the reputation of the council. </p>\n<p>But you must never have a close personal relationship with a child or young person under the age of 18, or 19 if still at school, or with an adult with care and support needs who you meet through work.</p>"}},"open":null,"link":null,"mediaLink":null},{"title":"New appointments and restricted posts","ariaLabel":null,"content":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>If you know someone who is applying for a post at the council, then you must not be involved in their recruitment process.</p>\n<p>Some council posts are politically restricted. This means the person in post can’t apply to become a member of a local authority or the House of Commons. Your director or a senior manager can tell you more about this.</p>"}},"open":null,"link":null,"mediaLink":null},{"title":"Working for another organisation","ariaLabel":null,"content":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>You must always tell your manager if you’re working for another organisation, or thinking about working for someone else at the same time as working for the council.</p>"}},"open":null,"link":null,"mediaLink":null},{"title":"Use of ICT equipment and social media at work","ariaLabel":null,"content":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>All ICT equipment belongs to the council and should always be used in the right way. You can get into trouble if you access any content that’s inappropriate or illegal or misuse equipment. </p>\n<p>Please take care using any technology at work such as mobile phones, text messages, emails, digital cameras, videos, web cams, websites and blogs.</p>\n<p>Always follow the council’s guidance on use of ICT and social media. Please read the Code of Conduct and <a href=\"https://buckinghamshire.itpolicysystem.com/acceptableuse.html\" title=\"ICT Policies\">ICT Policies</a> to find out more.</p>"}},"open":null,"link":null,"mediaLink":null},{"title":"Alcohol and drugs","ariaLabel":null,"content":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>We want the council to be a safe and healthy environment. Don’t bring drugs or alcohol into work, use them at work or be under the influence while at work. </p>\n<p>Read our <a href=\"//assets.ctfassets.net/fxzi1pcakms5/3ANfbzjWTXEvIkpNh4PMbl/e375157eb0bdba249811c70a1ac66683/BC_Code_of_Conduct_Services_Mar_2020.docx\">Code of Conduct</a> to find out more.</p>"}},"open":null,"link":null,"mediaLink":null}],"mediaLink":[{"id":"a3bba435-0073-5bed-8601-a49afa4424a2","type":"doc","title":"Code of Conduct","mediaLink":null,"description":null,"mediaFile":{"file":{"fileName":"BC Code of Conduct Services Mar 2020 (1).rtf","url":"//assets.ctfassets.net/fxzi1pcakms5/gN5IUSKGMQu2kP09foE8M/daf18a09bcfc8578851e299c884d5cd8/BC_Code_of_Conduct_Services_Mar_2020__1_.rtf"}}},{"id":"33531b66-126b-5307-af56-7ee560dff4bf","type":"doc","title":"Bullying and Harassment Guidance","mediaLink":null,"description":"BC Bullying & Harassment Guidance Mar 2020","mediaFile":{"file":{"fileName":"BC Bullying & Harrassment Guidance Mar 2020.doc","url":"//assets.ctfassets.net/fxzi1pcakms5/1ucI2VIDFb2jrHbcHZTtYd/88d4f7211341e0635ab507fb200838da/BC_Bullying___Harrassment_Guidance_Mar_2020.doc"}}}]}},"pageContext":{"id":"c46f43ce-d8cb-585c-861a-8def520a0959","map":{"510eff4f-2b1f-5b23-a329-8c19f43773ed":"holidays-and-time-off/annual-leave","d95dbc68-e229-5dd8-8a67-de32e90c3a11":"training-and-development/step-up-to-social-work","930fdc5f-ac67-506f-b847-6229569bf26a":"your-performance-at-work/your-performance-review","bead0121-d209-5eaa-907c-d64ca7a314a5":"training-and-development/upskilling-apprenticeships","458dc126-bc87-5700-af41-d7b61aff4a95":"training-and-development/new-talent-apprenticeships","a7172d78-188e-59fb-81f1-d49b18ca1979":"training-and-development/on-demand-manage